summary: RIGHT REAR SPRING HANGER RIPPED FROM FRAME LEAVING A HOLE IN THE FRAME. WITH THIS HANGER NOT ATTACHED TO FRAME THIS ALLOWED REAR AXLE TO MOVE 2 TO 3 INCHS FORWARD AND REARWARD. THIS ALSO PUT ADDITION STRESS ON THE CENTER HANGER AND ALSO ON BOTH SPRINGS ON THIS SIDE, IF THE REAR SPRING  HAD BROKEN OR THE CENTER HANGER HAD GIVEN WAY THE REAR AXLE WOULD HAVE TURN AROUND UNDER THE TRAILER.
